osted my skill to 68, which, according to my scientific estimations and rough guesses, should be accomplished in 2002 :-)<br><br>I'm looking forward to equip each of my rogue sister with a lockpick set by then.  I hope this answers any questions you may possibly have had about this esoteric topic :-)<br><br>May your skies be filled with fireworks every day!<br>*curtsies*<br>Soyin, <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ucutierogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cutierogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#660000>(2/15/02 3:03:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=275.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mechanized lockpicks</span><hr size=1> *cheers*  Thats excellent soyin!!  Count me in for buying one.  Ohh.. when can you make a telescope?  Im curious on what they do.  *smiles*<br><br>Arania<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/usoyinmilka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soyin Milka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#660000>(2/15/02 2:15:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=275.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mechanized lockpicks</span><hr size=1> Hello Arania :-)<br>Telescopes become trivial in the 90s and components to make them cost around 25 PPs.  They work like a magical item with an unlimited number of charges of the spell glimpse.  That's the item I'm the most looking forward to be able to make because I think it's pretty nifty.  My belt pouch will be filled with tinkered tools eventually ;-)  I think I'll be able to start making those in... 2002 ;-)<br><br>I shoul be rich enough to afford giving them away by the time I have the skill to make them.  Maybe I should not have said that...<br><br>Bah :-)<br>*bows and cracks her spine*<br>Soyin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uminuetthetalechaser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minuet the Talechaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#660000>(2/15/02 5:08:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=275.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mechanized lockpicks</span><hr size=1> I am not positive Soyin, but for some reason I seem to recall that even the bonus provided by tinkered lockpicks will not let you exceed the level cap. Might be worth a visit to the Safehouse to confirm. Of course all this means is your not going to be picking the locks in Charasis or the banks anytime soon. I think all the other doors, like City of Mist, can all be opened with a 200 skill.  Or 198, if you have some of Soyin's custom doohickeys!<br><br> <p>Minuet the Talechaser<br>The enchanting half-elf bard of Qeynos. <br>Circle of Sisters</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wiestrum>Wiestrum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sister</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#660000>(2/15/02 5:12:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=275.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www